Just Energy Group, Inc. (NYSE:JE) Position Decreased by Great West Life Assurance Co. Can


					Posted by Harper Lund on Jul 28th, 2017 // No Comments




Great West Life Assurance Co. Can reduced its stake in shares of  Just Energy Group, Inc. (NYSE:JE) (TSE:JE) by 67.6% during the first quarter, according to its most recent Form 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 20,067 shares of the utilities provider’s stock after selling 41,864 shares during the period. Great West Life Assurance Co. Can’s holdings in Just Energy Group were worth $125,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
A number of other institutional investors also recently added to or reduced their stakes in JE. Royce & Associates LP boosted its stake in  Just Energy Group by 5.9% in the fourth quarter. Royce & Associates LP now owns 26,720 shares of the utilities provider’s stock worth $146,000 after buying an additional 1,500 shares during the last quarter.  WFG Advisors LP purchased a new stake in  Just Energy Group during the fourth quarter worth approximately $223,000.  Dynamic Technology Lab Private Ltd boosted its stake in  Just Energy Group by 33.8% in the fourth quarter. Dynamic Technology Lab Private Ltd now owns 19,360 shares of the utilities provider’s stock worth $106,000 after buying an additional 4,886 shares during the last quarter.  Wells Fargo & Company MN boosted its stake in  Just Energy Group by 86.2% in the first quarter. Wells Fargo & Company MN now owns 32,982 shares of the utilities provider’s stock valued at $206,000 after buying an additional 15,273 shares during the period.  Finally, Guggenheim Capital LLC purchased a new stake in shares of  Just Energy Group during the fourth quarter worth about $124,000. Institutional investors and hedge funds own  29.12% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Just Energy Group Inc. alerts:



Just Energy Group, Inc. (NYSE:JE) traded up 2.06% during midday trading on Friday, hitting $5.44. 99,448 shares of the company were exchanged. The stock has a market capitalization of $799.75 million, a price-to-earnings ratio of 2.84 and a beta of 1.05. Just Energy Group, Inc. has a 1-year low of $4.83 and a 1-year high of $6.35. The stock has a 50 day moving average of $5.24 and a 200-day moving average of $5.71. 





Just Energy Group (NYSE:JE) (TSE:JE) last posted its quarterly earnings results on Wednesday, May 17th. The utilities provider reported $0.17 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.28 by $0.11. The firm had revenue of $715.64 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $815.35 million. Just Energy Group had a net margin of 12.37% and a negative return on equity of 84.39%.  Equities analysts expect that  Just Energy Group, Inc. will post $0.47 earnings per share for the current year. 
The business also recently disclosed a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Friday, June 30th. Investors of record on Thursday, June 15th were issued a $0.093 dividend. The ex-dividend date  was Tuesday, June 13th. This represents a $0.37 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 6.98%. Just Energy Group’s dividend payout ratio  is presently 23.57%. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION NOTICE: “Just Energy Group, Inc. (NYSE:JE) Position Decreased by Great West Life Assurance Co. Can” was first  published by Chaffey Breeze and is owned by of Chaffey Breeze. If you are reading this news story on another website, it was stolen and reposted in violation of U.S. and international trademark and copyright law. The legal version of this news story can be read at https://www.chaffeybreeze.com/2017/07/28/just-energy-group-inc-nyseje-shares-sold-by-great-west-life-assurance-co-can-updated-updated-updated.html. 
A number of equities research analysts have recently commented on JE shares. Canaccord Genuity cut shares of Just Energy Group from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a research report on Thursday, May 18th. FBR & Co  reaffirmed an “outperform” rating and set a $7.50 target price (down previously from $8.00) on shares of Just Energy Group in a research note on Friday, May 19th. HC Wainwright  reaffirmed a “buy” rating and set a $10.00 target price on shares of Just Energy Group in a research note on Wednesday, May 24th. ValuEngine lowered shares of Just Energy Group from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a research note on Tuesday, June 6th. Finally, Zacks Investment Research upgraded Just Energy Group from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating and set a $5.50 price objective for the company in a research report on Wednesday, July 12th. Four analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and three have issued  a buy rating to the company. The company presently has a consensus rating of “Hold” and an average target price of $8.25.
About Just Energy Group
Just Energy Group Inc (Just Energy) is an energy management solutions provider engaged in electricity, natural gas, solar and green energy. The Company’s segments include Consumer Energy and Commercial Energy. The Company operates in the United States, Canada and the United Kingdom, offering a range of energy products, including long-term fixed-price, variable rate and flat bill programs; home energy management services, including smart thermostats and tools to manage energy use at the appliance level, and residential solar panel installations.







