Just Energy Group, Inc. Ordinar (NYSE:JE) Experiences Heavy Trading Volume - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Just Energy Group, Inc. Ordinar (NYSE:JE) Experiences Heavy Trading Volume
July 17, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Just Energy Group, Inc. Ordinar shares had a trading volume of 165K in the last trading session.  Overall, volume was up 103.31% over the stocks normal daily volume. 
 These funds have also shifted positions in (JE).   James Investment Research Inc grew its investment by buying 100 shares an increase of 33.3%. James Investment Research Inc claims 400 shares valued at $2,000. The value of the position overall is down by 0.0%. As of quarter end Creative Planning had bought  a total of 9 shares growing its holdings by 0.0%. The value in dollars decreased from $157,000 to $131,000 a change of $26,000 for the reporting period.
 As of the end of the quarter Bank Of Montreal /can/ had acquired 83,500 shares growing its stake by 4.4%. The value of the investment in JE went from $11,828,000 to $10,338,000 a change of 12.6% since the last quarter. As of the end of the quarter Morgan Stanley had sold  a total of 199,264 shares trimming its position 99.3%. The value of the total investment in Just Energy Group, Inc. Ordinar went from $1,096,000 to $9,000 decreasing 99.2% quarter to quarter.
  On May 18 the stock rating was downgraded to “Hold” from “Buy” by analysts at Canaccord Genuity. On November 14, 2016 Canaccord Genuity started covering the stock with a rating of “Buy”.
 On December 18 analysts at FBR Capital starting coverage on JE with an initial rating of “Outperform” and a price target of $8.00. Equity analyst H.C. Wainwright initiated coverage on the stock giving it an initial rating of “Buy” and setting a price target of $10.00.





 H.C. Wainwright started covering JE by announcing an initial rating of “Buy” and establishing a price target of $7.25. On May 7 analysts at MLV & Co. released its first research report on the stock setting a rating of “Buy” and price target of $7.00.
 The company is so far trading up since yesterday’s close of $5.15.  The company also recently declared a dividend paid on Friday June 30th, 2017.  The dividend payment was $0.093 per share for the quarter or $0.37 annualized.  The dividend yield was $6.67.  The ex-dividend date was Tuesday the 13th of June 2017. 
 Shares are trading at $5.34 marginally under the 50 day moving average of $5.39 and slightly below the 200 day moving average of $5.73.  The 50 day moving average was down by -0.85% and the 200 day average moved down $-0.39. 
 Just Energy Group, Inc. Ordinar’s P/E ratio is 2.86 and market capitalization is 785.05M.  In the last earnings report the EPS was $1.86 and is estimated to be $0.46 for the current year with 147,013,000 shares currently outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is estimated at $-0.02 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $0.66. 
 Just Energy Group Inc., through its subsidiaries, provides electricity, natural gas, and solar and green energy in the United States, Canada, and the United Kingdom. The company operates through Consumer Energy, Commercial Energy, and Residential Solar divisions. It offers a range of energy products and home energy management services, including long-term fixed-price, variable-price, and flat-bill programs; and residential solar panel installations, as well as sells smart thermostats. The company also sells residential solar finance products; and acts as an originator of residential solar deals. As of May 5, 2016, it served approximately 1.8 million residential and commercial customers. The company sells its products through broker channel using the commercial platform, door-to-door commercial independent contractors, and commercial sales representatives. Just Energy Group Inc. was founded in 1997 and is headquartered in Mississauga, Canada..






