Just Energy Group, Inc. Ordinar (NYSE:JE) Experiences Light Trading Volume 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsJust Energy Group, Inc. Ordinar (NYSE:JE) Experiences Light Trading Volume
July 26, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



Just Energy Group, Inc. Ordinar shares had a trading volume of 8,372 on Tuesday.  Overall, volume was down 89.66% under the stocks normal daily volume. 
 Here are a few additional firms who have increased or decreased their stake in (JE).   Dorchester Wealth Management Co augmented its holdings by buying 41,850 shares an increase of 49.4% from 03/31/2017 to 06/30/2017. Dorchester Wealth Management Co now controls 126,575 shares with a value of $663,000. The value of the position overall is up by 24.6%. As of quarter end Advisors Capital Management, LLC had acquired  a total of 13,661 shares growing its stake by 0.7%. The value in dollars decreased from $12,325,000 to $10,388,000 decreasing 15.7% quarter over quarter.
 James Investment Research Inc bolstered its stake by buying 100 shares an increase of 33.3%. James Investment Research Inc claims 400 shares worth $2,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 0.0%. Creative Planning expanded its position by buying 9 shares an increase of 0.0% in the quarter. Creative Planning currently owns 25,009 shares valued at $131,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 16.6%.
  On May 18 the company was rated “Hold” according to a Canaccord Genuity report which was a cut from the previous “Buy” rating. On November 14, 2016 Canaccord Genuity initiated coverage on the stock setting a rating of “Buy”.
 On December 18 analysts at FBR Capital initiated coverage on JE with an initial rating of “Outperform” and a price target of $8.00. Equity analyst H.C. Wainwright starting coverage on JE by announcing an initial rating of “Buy” and projecting a price target of $10.00.        Advertisement






 H.C. Wainwright added JE to its research portfolio with a rating of “Buy” and price target of $7.25. Equity analyst MLV & Co. started covering the stock giving it an initial rating of “Buy” and establishing a price target of $7.00.
 The company is trading unchanged from yesterday’s close of $5.31.  The company also announced a dividend which was paid on Friday the 30th of June 2017.  The dividend was $0.093 per share for the quarter which comes to $0.37 on an annualized basis.  This dividend amount represented a yeild of $6.67.  The ex-dividend date was Tuesday the 13th of June 2017. 
 Shares of the company are trading at $5.31 just a bit higher than the 50 day moving average of $5.23 and just below the 200 day moving average of $5.71.  The 50 day moving average was up $0.08 and the 200 day average was down $-0.40. 
 The P/E ratio is currently 2.77 and the market cap is 780.64M.  As of the latest earnings report the EPS was $1.92 and is estimated to be $0.47 for the current year with 147,013,000 shares now outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is estimated at $-0.02 with next year’s EPS anticipated to be $0.67. 
 Just Energy Group Inc., through its subsidiaries, provides electricity, natural gas, and solar and green energy in the United States, Canada, and the United Kingdom. The company operates through Consumer Energy, Commercial Energy, and Residential Solar divisions. It offers a range of energy products and home energy management services, including long-term fixed-price, variable-price, and flat-bill programs; and residential solar panel installations, as well as sells smart thermostats. The company also sells residential solar finance products; and acts as an originator of residential solar deals. As of May 5, 2016, it served approximately 1.8 million residential and commercial customers. The company sells its products through broker channel using the commercial platform, door-to-door commercial independent contractors, and commercial sales representatives. Just Energy Group Inc. was founded in 1997 and is headquartered in Mississauga, Canada..
